FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 1 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 ARTICLE I PURPOSE 1.01 General. The purpose of this Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services (the "Tariff") is to provide a framework and set forth terms, conditions, and Service Schedules for the sale of specified Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services by FirstEnergy Solutions Corp., ("FirstEnergy"). 1.02 Offer to Sell Ancillary Services. FirstEnergy offers to sell Ancillary Services to Customers from time to time in accordance with, and subject to, the terms and conditions set forth in this Tariff when such services are needed or useful to support the transmission of capacity and energy from resources to loads. Ancillary Services are available under this Tariff in connection with (1) sales to a regional transmission organization ("RTO") such as an independent transmission organization or transco i.e., where the RTO has no ability to self-supply Ancillary Services but instead depends on third parties; (2) sales to a FirstEnergy Operating Company (except to the extent that such sales utilize the ATSI Transmission System); or (3) sales to a public utility that is purchasing Ancillary Services to satisfy its own Open Access Tariff Requirements to offer Ancillary Services to its own customers. 1.03 Offer to Sell Interconnected Operations Services. FirstEnergy offers to sell Interconnected Operations Services to Customers from time to time in accordance with, and subject
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 2 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 to, the terms and conditions set forth in this Tariff when such services are needed or useful to support the transmission of capacity and energy from resources to loads. Interconnected Operations Services are available under this Tariff in connection with (1) sales to a regional transmission organization ("RTO") such as an independent transmission organization or transco i.e., where the RTO has no ability to self-supply Interconnected Operations Services but instead depends on third parties; (2) sales to a FirstEnergy Operating Company or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the ATSI Transmission System; or (3) sales to a public utility that is purchasing Interconnected Operations Services to be able to supply Interconnected Operations Services to its own customers. ARTICLE II DEFINITIONS When used herein, in an attached service schedule, or in an executed Service Agreement or Specifications under this Tariff, the terms sets forth below shall have the following meanings. 2.01 AAA: The American Arbitration Association. 2.02 Affiliate: With respect to any person, any other person (other than an individual) or entity that directly or indirectly, through one or more intermediaries, controls, or is controlled by or is under common control with, such person or entity. For the purposes of the foregoing definition, "control" means the direct or indirect ownership of more than 50 percent of the outstanding capital stock or other equity interests having ordinary voting power.
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 3 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 2.03 American Transmission Systems, Incorporated ("ATSI"). A transmission owner that does not own or control generation resources and that provides transmission and Ancillary Services over the ATSI Transmission System pursuant to the ATSI Open Access Transmission Tariff. 2.04 Ancillary Services: Those services that are necessary or useful to support the transmission of Capacity and/or Energy from resources to loads while maintaining reliable operation of the transmission provider's transmission system in accordance with Good Electric Operating Practice. Ancillary Services available under this Tariff include Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service, Regulation and Frequency Response Service, Energy Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning Reserve Service, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental Reserve Service. 2.05 Applicant: An entity that has submitted a complete Application to enter into a Service Agreement under this Tariff. 2.06 Application: An application for service under this Tariff in the form attached hereto as Attachment A. 2.07 ATSI Open Access Transmission Tariff: An Open Access Transmission Tariff filed at the FERC on behalf of ATSI, or its successor transmission tariff. 2.08 ATSI Transmission System: The facilities of ATSI over which transmission services are available pursuant to the ATSI Open Access Transmission Tariff.
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 4 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 2.09 Authorized Representative: The person(s) designated in writing by the Parties to enter into Transactions under their Service Agreement(s). 2.10 Business Day: Any day on which Federal Reserve member banks in New York City are open for business. 2.11 Capacity: The resource that produces electric energy, measured in megawatts. 2.12 Contract Price: The price at which FirstEnergy agrees to sell Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services to Customer, and at which Customer agrees to purchase Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services from FirstEnergy, in a Transaction under this Tariff. 2.13 Contract Quantity: The quantity of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services which FirstEnergy agrees to sell to Customer, and which Customer agrees to purchase from FirstEnergy, in a Transaction under this Tariff. 2.14 Customer: Any person with which FirstEnergy has entered into a Service Agreement under this Tariff. 2.15 Day: A twenty-four hour period commencing at twelve o'clock midnight prevailing time in Akron, Ohio, and ending at the next following twelve o'clock midnight. 2.16 Delivery Point(s): The physical point or points of delivery of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services to either Party as agreed in the Specifications.
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 5 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 2.17 ECAR: East Central Area Reliability Coordination Agreement, a regional reliability council of NERC, or its successor. 2.18 Energy: Electric energy delivered under this Tariff at three-phase, 60-hertz alternating current, measured in megawatt hours. 2.19 Energy Imbalance Service: Energy Imbalance Service is provided when a difference occurs between the scheduled and the actual delivery of energy to a load located in a control area over a single hour. 2.20 FERC: The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission or its regulatory successor. 2.21 FirstEnergy Corp.: FirstEnergy Corp., a public utility holding company organized and existing under the laws of the State of Ohio. 2.22 FirstEnergy Operating Companies: The FirstEnergy Operating Companies are wholly-owned public utility company subsidiaries of FirstEnergy Corp. They are: The Cleveland Electric Illuminating Company, an Ohio corporation; The Toledo Edison Company, an Ohio corporation; Ohio Edison Company, an Ohio corporation; and Pennsylvania Power Company, a Pennsylvania corporation, is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Ohio Edison Company and an indirect subsidiary of FirstEnergy Corp. Each of the FirstEnergy Operating Companies owns and operates facilities for the generation, distribution and sale of electric power and energy to retail and wholesale customers.
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 6 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 2.23 Force Majeure: Any cause beyond the reasonable control of, and not the result of negligence or the lack of diligence of, the Party claiming Force Majeure or its contractors or suppliers. It includes, without limitation, earthquake, storm, lightning, flood, backwater caused by flood, fire, explosion, act of the public enemy, epidemic, accident, failure of facilities, equipment or fuel supply, acts of God, war, riot, civil disturbances, strike, labor disturbances, labor or material shortage, national emergency, restraint by court order or other public authority or governmental agency, interruption of synchronous operation, or other similar or dissimilar causes beyond the control of the Party affected, which causes such Party could not have avoided by exercising Good Electric Operating Practice. Nothing contained herein shall be construed to require a Party to settle any strike, lockout, work stoppage, or other industrial disturbance or dispute in which it may be involved or to take an appeal from any judicial, regulatory or administrative action. 2.24 Generator Imbalance Service. Generator Imbalance Service is provided when a difference occurs over a single hour between the amount of Energy scheduled for delivery from a generator connected directly to the transmission system of a transmission provider and the amount of Energy actually delivered from that generator to the transmission system during such hour. 2.25 Good Electric Operating Practice: The practices, methods, and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electric power industry during the relevant time period or the
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 7 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 practices, methods, and acts which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result consistent with reliability, safety, expedition, the requirements of governmental agencies having jurisdiction, and, if appropriate or relevant under the Transaction in question, at a reasonable cost. Such term is not intended to be limited to the optimum practice, method, or act to the exclusion of all others, but rather to constitute a spectrum of acceptable practices, methods, or acts. FirstEnergy may not enter into a contract that will violate any guideline, standard, or criteria of ECAR, NERC, or their successors. 2.26 Hour: The 60 minute period commencing at the beginning of a clock hour. 2.27 Interconnected Operations Services : Loss Compensation Service and Generator Imbalance Service. 2.28 Interest Rate: The lesser of Prime Rate plus two percent and the maximum lawful rate permitted by applicable law. 2.29 Loss Compensation Service: Capacity and Energy supplied to compensate for capacity and energy losses that occur when a transmission provider delivers electricity across its transmission facilities and/or its distribution facilities. 2.30 Month: All of the days in any calendar month, or if a reservation starts on any day other than the first day of the month, the number of days remaining in the month in which the

Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 reservation commences. 2.31 NERC: The North American Electric Reliability Council, or its successor. 2.32 Off-Peak Period: The observed legal holidays and all other periods not described as the on-peak period included in the definition of Section 2.35 shall be the off-peak period. 2.33 On-Peak Period: The on-peak period shall be from 7:00 a.m. to 11:00 p.m. prevailing time in Akron, Ohio Monday through Friday, except for the following legal holidays observed during this period: New Year's Day, Memorial Day, Independence Day, Labor Day, Thanksgiving Day and Christmas Day. 2.34 Open Access Transmission Tariff: A tariff filed by a transmission provider with the FERC in accordance with FERC Order No. 888 pursuant to which transmission services will be made available over its transmission system to eligible customers on a non-discriminatory basis. 2.35 Operating Reserve-Spinning Reserve Service: Reserve generation capacity provided by generating units that are on-line and loaded at less then maximum output that may be needed to serve load immediately in the event of a system contingency. 2.36 Operating Reserve-Supplemental Reserve Service: Reserve generation capacity provided by generating units that are on-line but not fully loaded, by quick-start generation or by interruptible load that may be needed to serve load within a short period of time in the event of a system contingency.

Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 2.37 Out-of-Pocket Costs ("OPC"): As it applies to Transactions under this Tariff, all expenses incurred by FirstEnergy that would not otherwise have been incurred if the Transaction had not been arranged. Such expenses include, but are not limited to, costs associated with fuel, variable operation, variable maintenance, startup, shutdown, minimum run, taxes, minimum load, SO2, and other emission allowances, transmission losses, charges for any Capacity and Energy purchased, or charges of a similar or dissimilar nature, which are reasonably allocated by FirstEnergy to such a Transaction. ARTICLE III SERVICE AGREEMENTS 3.01 Prerequisite to Service. In order for a Customer to take Ancillary Services and/or Interconnected Operations Services under this Tariff, a Service Agreement must be executed by FirstEnergy and the Customer and filed, as required, with FERC. The Customer will cooperate with FirstEnergy and provide information necessary for FirstEnergy to proceed with any such required filing. FirstEnergy will tender the Service Agreement for filing with FERC, as required, in accordance with FERC rules and requirements. 3.02 Effective Date. Service Agreements executed under this Tariff shall become effective on the date specified in the Service Agreement, or on such other date as assigned by FERC. 3.03 Termination. A Service Agreement may be terminated by either Party upon thirty (30) days prior written notice, provided, however, that the Service Agreement will remain in effect until all Transactions previously agreed upon or entered into are completed. ARTICLE IV SERVICES TO BE RENDERED 4.01 Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services. FirstEnergy will sell Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services under this Tariff when FirstEnergy and a
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 12 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 Customer have reached agreement on the terms and conditions for a specific Transaction. All Transactions between the Parties shall be at rates, terms and conditions set forth in Service Schedules A through H, and shall be subject to the availability of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services and of transmission service necessary to complete the Transaction. Neither Party commits, by entering into a Service Agreement, to enter into any individual Transaction with the other Party. Except to the extent provided by law or regulatory requirement, no undertaking by one Party to the other under any provision of this Tariff or Service Agreement shall be deemed to constitute the dedication of its system or any portion thereof to the public or to the other Party, and it is agreed that any undertaking to perform a Transaction by any Party shall cease upon completion of the Transaction. 4.02 Conditions of Service. Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services shall be made available hereunder consistent with Good Electric Operating Practice, including, but not limited to, applicable NERC and ECAR requirements, and FirstEnergy's performance hereunder shall be excused in the event that Force Majeure prevents FirstEnergy from providing such services. References to "Point-to-Point Transmission Service" and "Network Integration Service" have the meanings provided under the Open Access Transmission Tariff of any transmission provider with respect to which Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services are being acquired.
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 13 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 ARTICLE V ELIGIBILITY FOR SERVICE 5.01 Application. Before a Customer takes Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services under this Tariff, it must enter into a Service Agreement with FirstEnergy. To apply for service, a Customer must complete and submit an Application, in the form attached hereto as Attachment A, to the following: Manager, Wholesale Energy Transactions FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. 395 Ghent Road Akron, Ohio 44333 or such other person as may be designated in writing by FirstEnergy from time to time. 5.02 Creditworthiness and Security. To determine the ability of the Customer to meet its obligations related to service hereunder, FirstEnergy may subject the Customer's Application to reasonable credit review procedures. In addition, FirstEnergy may require a Customer to provide and maintain in effect during the term of the Service Agreement an unconditional and irrevocable letter of credit, a parental guaranty, or an alternative form of security acceptable to FirstEnergy and consistent with commercial practices that protects FirstEnergy against the risk of the Customer's non-payment. FirstEnergy reserves the right to request the Customer to submit to FirstEnergy updated financial information to permit FirstEnergy to evaluate the Customer's creditworthiness on an on-going basis.
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 14 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 If the Customer fails to meet FirstEnergy's credit review standards or provide one of the payment guarantee options above, FirstEnergy may refuse to provide Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services or discontinue Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services until such time as FirstEnergy is assured of the Customer's ability to pay. FirstEnergy may request any other information that it requires to evaluate the Customer's Application or continued eligibility for service. 5.03 Limitation. FirstEnergy is not required to enter into a Service Agreement with a potential customer and may suspend Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services hereunder if the Customer commits or experiences an Event of Default as defined in Article XVI of this Tariff, provided, however, that FirstEnergy may continue to provide Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services if the Customer pays for such Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services in advance or furnishes good and sufficient security of a continuing nature in an amount at least equal to the cost of such Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services. 5.04 Sales to Affiliates. FirstEnergy may make sales of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services to other FirstEnergy Affiliates only after FERC has accepted a Service Agreement with the Affiliate in a separate rate filing made pursuant to Section 205 of the
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 15 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 Federal Power Act. 5.05 Sales Among FirstEnergy Operating Companies. FirstEnergy may make sales of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services to a FirstEnergy Operating Company only after FERC has accepted a Service Agreement with such FirstEnergy Operating Company in a separate rate filing made pursuant to Section 205 of the Federal Power Act. ARTICLE VI TRANSMISSION SERVICES 6.01 Transmission Service. Transmission services for a Transaction under this Tariff will be provided by a transmission provider under the rates, terms, and conditions contained in the transmission provider's Open Access Transmission Tariff. 6.02 Transmission Service on ATSI Transmission System. Either FirstEnergy or Customer may arrange for transmission service on the ATSI Transmission System pursuant to the ATSI Open Access Transmission Tariff. Unless otherwise agreed, the Party arranging for such transmission service will assume full responsibility for that service. When FirstEnergy takes service over the ATSI Transmission System under the ATSI Open Access Transmission Tariff in order to deliver Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services to Customer under this Tariff, FirstEnergy will pay the same rates for transmission, Ancillary Services and other services as are charged to other ATSI Open Access Transmission Tariff customers for the same type, length, and
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 16 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 magnitude of transmission service at the time such Transactions occur and will separately state in its bill to the Customer the prices for each of the components of the Transaction. 6.03 Transmission Service on Third-Party Transmission Systems. Unless otherwise agreed between FirstEnergy and the Customer, the Customer shall arrange for transmission service on any third party's transmission system required to support a Transaction under this Tariff and shall bear all costs associated with such transmission service. If FirstEnergy arranges for any such transmission service, unless otherwise agreed, the Customer shall reimburse FirstEnergy for any third party transmission costs incurred in the Transaction. ARTICLE VII AVAILABILITY AND SALE OF ANCILLARY SERVICES AND INTERCONNECTED OPERATIONS SERVICES 7.01 General. At any time during the term of an executed Service Agreement, FirstEnergy may notify Customer that Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services are available. The terms and conditions for any Transaction shall be in accordance with this Tariff and as otherwise agreed to by the Parties in advance of the Transaction. 7.02 Authorized Representatives. Each Party shall designate one or more Authorized Representatives who shall be authorized to act on its behalf with respect to those matters set forth herein which are the functions and responsibilities of the Authorized Representatives; within thirty days after execution of a Service Agreement, each Party shall give written notice to the other Party of

Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 its designation. All arrangements for Transactions shall be made between the Authorized Representatives of FirstEnergy and Customer. Authorized Representatives shall have no authority to unilaterally modify any of the provisions of this Tariff or a Service Agreement. 7.03 Specification of Transaction Terms and Conditions. Except as set forth in Section 7.04, the specific terms of a Transaction to be established by the Parties for each Transaction shall be documented in written Specifications, substantially in the form annexed hereto as Attachment C, executed by the Parties prior to commencement of the Transaction. FirstEnergy shall document in the Specifications the terms and conditions of each Transaction of more than one day in duration and telecopy it to Customer by the next business day after reaching verbal agreement, and prior to the commencement of the Transaction. The Specifications associated with each Transaction shall constitute an integral part of the Service Agreement and shall be read and construed as one with the Service Agreement and this Tariff. Any conflict not reasonably capable of reconciliation, among this Tariff, a Service Agreement, and the Specifications shall be resolved in favor of the Tariff. 7.04 Short-Term Transactions. To meet the needs of the Parties, the Parties' Authorized Representatives may verbally agree on terms and conditions for Transactions which do not exceed one day (twenty-four hours). The terms and conditions of such Transactions agreed to by the authorized Representatives shall be those terms contained in a tape recording of the Authorized
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 18 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 Representatives in which they agree to said terms and conditions. Such Transactions shall promptly be confirmed in writing by the Authorized Representatives if requested by either Party. 7.05 Recording. Each Party consents to the recording of all telephone conversations between its Authorized Representatives and agrees to obtain any necessary consent from, and give notice of such recording to, its Authorized Representatives. Any properly authenticated recordings of such telephone conversations may be introduced as evidence in any legal proceeding to establish proof of any matter relating to a Transaction under this Tariff. The Parties agree not to contest or assert any defense to the validity or enforceability of a Transaction established by properly authenticated recordings of telephone conversations under laws relating to whether certain agreements are to be in writing and signed by the Party to be bound thereby. 7.06 Emergency Curtailment or Interruption. In the event of sudden or emergency curtailment or interruption of Transactions hereunder, the Party experiencing or affected by such interruption or curtailment shall so notify the other Party's schedulers or dispatchers, and any third party involved with the delivery of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services pursuant to a Transaction, in as timely a manner as possible. ARTICLE VIII SERVICE CONDITIONS 8.01 All Transactions Voluntary and on an As-Available Basis. All Transactions under

Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 this Tariff shall be voluntary and subject to the availability of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services to complete the Transaction. Except to the extent required by law or regulatory requirement, FirstEnergy does not warrant that it has any Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services available for sale hereunder and does not commit to enter into any individual Transaction with any Customer unless agreed to pursuant to Article VII. Title to, and risk of loss associated with, Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services scheduled hereunder shall transfer from FirstEnergy to Customer at the Delivery Points. 8.04 Service Terms and Conditions. All Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services provided hereunder shall be delivered and billed in accordance with the applicable Service Schedule and the agreed upon terms and conditions of a particular Transaction. 8.05 FirstEnergy Responsibilities. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 ARTICLE IX REMEDIES FOR NON-PERFORMANCE 9.01 Excuses for Non-Performance. A Party may be excused from delivering, or accepting Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services only for reasons of Force Majeure or under the specific circumstances to which the Parties have agreed in the Specifications under which either Party may interrupt without liability. In the event a Party interrupts Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services for reasons other than those authorized herein, the interrupting Party shall have the obligations set forth in Section 9.02 of this Tariff. 9.02 Interruptions of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services. With respect to the unauthorized failure to schedule, accept, deliver, or receive Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services, in whole or in part, in accordance with this Tariff: (a) As an alternative to the damages provisions of Section 9.02(b) below, if the Parties both agree, the nonperforming Party may supply or accept Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services, as the case may be, pursuant to such terms as the Parties agree in order to discharge some or all of the obligation to pay damages. In the absence of such agreement, the damages provisions of Section 9.02(b) shall apply. (b) In the event FirstEnergy fails to supply the Contract Quantity, where such failure was not excused by Force Majeure, by the specific circumstances to which the Parties have agreed in writing, or by Customer, then FirstEnergy shall pay Customer, on the date payment would otherwise be due in accordance with this Tariff an amount for each unit of such deficiency equal to the positive difference between (i) the price at which Customer is or would be able to obtain comparable supplies of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services at a commercially reasonable price (as
FirstEnergy Solutions Corp. Original Sheet No. 22 Tariff for Sales of Ancillary Services And Interconnected Operations Services Issued by: E.C. Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 adjusted to reflect differences in transmission costs, if any) and (ii) the applicable Contract Price. In the event Customer fails to accept or receive the Contract Quantity, where such failure was not excused by Force Majeure, by the specific circumstances to which the Parties have agreed in writing, or by FirstEnergy, then Customer shall pay FirstEnergy on the date payment would otherwise be due in accordance with this Tariff an amount for each unit of such deficiency equal to the positive difference between (i) the applicable Contract Price and (ii) the price at which FirstEnergy is or would be able to sell comparable supplies of Ancillary Services and Interconnected Operations Services at a commercially reasonable price (as adjusted to reflect differences in transmission costs, if any). The Parties agree further that the non- performing Party will pay the aggrieved Party any amounts due under this Section 9.02(b) within the time for payment specified in Section 11.02. (c) Both Parties hereby stipulate that the damages set forth in Section 9.02(b) are reasonable in light of the anticipated harm and the difficulty of estimation or calculation of actual damages and each Party hereby waives the right to contest such damages as an unreasonable penalty. (d) In the event either Customer or FirstEnergy fails to pay to the other Party any amounts in accordance with Section 9.02(b) when due, the aggrieved Party shall have the right to suspend performance under the Transaction for which such amounts are due or any other Transactions until such amounts, plus interest at the Interest Rate, have been paid, and/or exercise any remedy available at law or in equity to enforce payment of such amount plus interest. ARTICLE X RECORDS 10.01 Records Retention. Each Party to a Transaction shall maintain written records consisting of, but not limited to, capacity reserved, energy supplied, Transaction times, and Transaction pricing. These records shall be retained for a period of six (6) years from the conclusion

Stein Manager, Electric Trading and Operations Issued On: September 29, 2000 Effective Date: September 1, 2000 of the Transaction. 10.02 Inspection and Audit. Each Party shall make such records available for inspection and audit by the other Party at reasonable times and places at the other Party's request. ARTICLE XI BILLING AND PAYMENT 11.01 Billing Statement. Each month, FirstEnergy will prepare and render to the Customer a billing statement and invoice for services. The accounting period for Transactions will be one calendar month. Unless otherwise agreed by the Parties, each monthly bill for charges under this Tariff will be rendered by the fifth working day in the month following the calendar month in which the charges were incurred. Unless otherwise agreed by the Parties, bills will be electronically transmitted to the Customer, to be followed by a mailed invoice. 11.02 Payment Date. When prepayment is not required, payment will be due and payable not later than the first business day following the nineteenth day of the month (the "Payment Date"). Unless otherwise agreed in writing, all payments must be wire transferred to an account designated in writing by FirstEnergy from time to time. 11.03 Failure to Pay. In the event the Customer fails to make full payment of a bill rendered under the Tariff on or before the Payment Date, FirstEnergy will notify the Customer of the delinquency (by mail, fax, or e-mail), and the Customer will have five (5) days from the date of

Services to Be Rendered Energy Imbalance Service is provided when a difference occurs between the scheduled and the actual delivery of energy to a load located within a Control Area over a single hour. A transmission customer purchasing transmission service pursuant to an Open Access Transmission Tariff must either purchase this service from its transmission provider or make alternative comparable arrangements to satisfy its Energy Imbalance Service obligation. The Energy Imbalance Service offered by FirstEnergy is intended to enable Customer to meet this obligation. The Open Access Transmission Tariff of each transmission provider generally establishes a deviation band of the scheduled transaction which is to be applied hourly to any energy imbalance that occurs as a result of the scheduled transaction(s) on its system. The applicable deviation band and any other terms affecting the quantity of Energy Imbalance Service to be supplied by FirstEnergy shall be set forth in the Specifications between FirstEnergy and Customer. Parties should attempt to eliminate energy imbalances within the limits of the deviation band by returning energy in like kind by the end of the next billing cycle. Energy imbalances outside the deviation band established by a transmission provider pursuant to its Open Access Transmission Tariff and energy imbalances not corrected by the end of the next billing cycle will be subject to charges set forth below.
